ment's fallback path writes to an unexpected artifact slot or clears existing entries — this only surfaces when implement is wired to an artifact store that holds other artifacts. REAL-INFRA: An in-process fake store with pre-seeded artifacts (no `grounding` key) is sufficient to detect both the missing fallback output and any corruption. LLM-DEP: The behavior tested is fallback routing and artifact safety, not generation quality — deterministic stub output suffices. REJECTION-GATE for Unit: 'without corrupting other stored artifacts' requires verifying the full store state after execution, which requires the store to be wired up.","test_description":"Seed a fake artifact store with several pre-existing artifact keys (e.g., `diagnosis`, `plan`) but no `grounding` key. Run implement with a stubbed LLM. Assert: (a) a valid `plan` artifact is written, (b) all other pre-seeded artifacts remain at their original values, (c) no exception or panic is raised.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.28,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.01}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9923,"cache_read_input_tokens":3199,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9923},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"867d1673-beaf-4c93-bfeb-10677a93b57b","uuid":"8544ab70-d2ed-4b0f-a8c7-5e08f8fd44b6"}
